bighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Arllechwedd,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["German: occupational name for a ferryman, Middle High German <i>verje</i>, <i>verge</i>."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gwladus","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old form of   Gladys  , of uncertain derivation."],"variants":[{"name":"Gwladys","meanings":["Old form of   Gladys  , of uncertain derivation."]}]},{"name":"Moel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, composed of two different Hebrew elements, <i>Yah(weh)</i> and <i>El</i>, both of which mean ‘God’ the implication of the name is that the Hebrew God, <i>Yahweh</i>, is the only true god. This is a common name in the Bible, being borne by, among others, one of King David's ‘mighty men’ (1 Chronicles 11:38), and a minor prophet who lived in the 8th century  bc . The name has been perennially popular as a Jewish name; it was also taken up by the Puritans and other Christian fundamentalists. The name has long been in regular use in North America but was uncommon in Britain until the 1990s. Well-known bearers of the name include the American singer and entertainer  Joel Grey  (  b. 1932 ), the West Indian cricketer  Joel Garner  (  b. 1952 ), and the American film director  Joel Coen  (  b. 1954 ). The French form  <b>Joël</b>  is also used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwladus Moel ferch Hywel was born in Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Hywel ap Dafydd. She had at least 2 daughters with Seincyn \"Jenkin\" Deca ap Madog Ddu ap Gruffudd."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1310":"1310","1340":"1340","of,Maelor Gymraeg,Denbighshire,Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Arllechwedd,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1310":"1310","1340":"1340","of,Maelor Gymraeg,Denbighshire,Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of,Arllechwedd,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1310":"1310","1340":"1340","of,Maelor Gymraeg,Denbighshire,Wales":"Denbighshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","of,Arllechwedd,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Gwladus Moel ferch Hywel est née à Caernarfonshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, fille de Hywel ap Dafydd. Elle a eu au moins 2 filles avec Seincyn \"Jenkin\" Deca ap Madog Ddu ap Gruffudd."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1340–Female":"1340–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1310":"1310","1340":"1340","of,Maelor Gymraeg,Denbighshire,Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of,Arllechwedd,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Gwladus Moel ferch Hywel wurde in Caernarfonshire, Wales, United King